36#include "krb5_locl.h"
37
38KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
39krb5_rd_error(krb5_context context,
40 const krb5_data *msg,
41 KRB_ERROR *result)
42{
43
44 size_t len;
45 krb5_error_code ret;
46
47 ret = decode_KRB_ERROR(msg->data, msg->length, result, &len);
48 if(ret) {
49 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
50 return ret;
51 }
52 result->error_code += KRB5KDC_ERR_NONE;
53 return 0;
54}
55
56KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION void KRB5_LIB_CALL
57krb5_free_error_contents (krb5_context context,
58 krb5_error *error)
59{
60 free_KRB_ERROR(error);
61 memset(error, 0, sizeof(*error));
62}
63
64KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION void KRB5_LIB_CALL
65krb5_free_error (krb5_context context,
66 krb5_error *error)
67{
68 krb5_free_error_contents (context, error);
69 free (error);
70}
71
72KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
73krb5_error_from_rd_error(krb5_context context,
74 const krb5_error *error,
75 const krb5_creds *creds)
76{
77 krb5_error_code ret;
78
79 ret = error->error_code;
80 if (error->e_text != NULL) {
81 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "%s", *error->e_text);
82 } else {
83 char clientname[256], servername[256];
84
85 if (creds != NULL) {
86 krb5_unparse_name_fixed(context, creds->client,
87 clientname, sizeof(clientname));
88 krb5_unparse_name_fixed(context, creds->server,
89 servername, sizeof(servername));
90 }
91
92 switch (ret) {
93 case KRB5KDC_ERR_NAME_EXP :
94 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
95 N_("Client %s%s%s expired", ""),
96 creds ? "(" : "",
97 creds ? clientname : "",
98 creds ? ")" : "");
99 break;
100 case KRB5KDC_ERR_SERVICE_EXP :
101 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
102 N_("Server %s%s%s expired", ""),
103 creds ? "(" : "",
104 creds ? servername : "",
105 creds ? ")" : "");
106 break;
107 case KRB5KDC_ERR_C_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN :
108 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
109 N_("Client %s%s%s unknown", ""),
110 creds ? "(" : "",
111 creds ? clientname : "",
112 creds ? ")" : "");
113 break;
114 case KRB5KDC_ERR_S_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN :
115 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
116 N_("Server %s%s%s unknown", ""),
117 creds ? "(" : "",
118 creds ? servername : "",
119 creds ? ")" : "");
120 break;
121 default :
122 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
123 break;
124 }
125 }
126 return ret;
127}
